    "source_sections": {
      "references": "[Er50c] Erd\\H{o}s, P., Az $1/x_1 + 1/x_2 + \\ldots + 1/x_n =A/B$ egyenlet eg\\'{e}sz sz\\'{a}m\\'{u} megold\\'{a}sair\\'{o}l. Mat. Lapok (1950), 192-210.\n \n [Vo85] Vose, Michael D., Egyptian fractions. Bull. London Math. Soc. (1985), 21-24.\n \n [vDTa25b] W. van Doorn and Q. Tang, The smallest denominator not contained in a unit fraction decomposition of 1 with fixed length. arXiv:2512.22083 (2025).",
      "remarks": "Erd\\H{o}s \\cite{Er50c} proved that\\[\\log\\log b \\ll N(b) \\ll \\frac{\\log b}{\\log\\log b}.\\]The upper bound was improved by Vose \\cite{Vo85} to\\[N(b) \\ll \\sqrt{\\log b}.\\]One can also investigate the average of $N(a,b)$ for fixed $b$, and it is known that\\[\\frac{1}{b}\\sum_{1\\leq a<b}N(a,b) \\gg \\log\\log b.\\]Related to [18]. There is also a close connection to [293] (particularly with $N(b-1,b)$), as elucidated by van Doorn and Tang \\cite{vDTa25b}.\n\nThis problem has been formalised in Lean as part of the Google DeepMind Formal Conjectures project."
    },
