    "ambiguity_status": "minor",
    "intended": "For integers $1\\leq a<b$ let $N(a,b)$ denote the minimal $k$ such that there exist integers $1<n_1<\\cdots<n_k$ with\\[\\frac{a}{b}=\\frac{1}{n_1}+\\cdots+\\frac{1}{n_k}.\\]Estimate $N(b)=\\max_{1\\leq a<b}N(a,b)$. Is it true that $N(b) \\ll \\log\\log b$?",
